        "title": "Govt supports distribution of 22 lakh farm machines under Sub-Mission on Agricultural Mechanisation",
        "summary": "Government has supported the distribution of around 22 lakh agricultural machines worth nine thousand 404 crore rupees to individual farmers so far across the country under the Sub-Mission on Agricultural Mechanisation. The mission was launched in 2014-15 to promote farm mechanisation, which plays a critical role in enhancing agricultural productivity in the country. &#160; It […]",
        "article": "Government has supported the distribution of around 22 lakh agricultural machines worth nine thousand 404 crore rupees to individual farmers so far across the country under the Sub-Mission on Agricultural Mechanisation. The mission was launched in 2014-15 to promote farm mechanisation, which plays a critical role in enhancing agricultural productivity in the country. &nbsp; It involves using machines, equipment, and modern technologies for agricultural operations across the crop production cycle. These operations include land preparation, sowing, irrigation, plant protection, harvesting, and post-harvest management. Special emphasis has been placed on underserved and North-Eastern States to address regional disparities in access to farm machinery and technology. Around 41 thousand drone demonstrations were conducted with over 52 crore rupees in financial support, promoting precision agriculture adoption nationwide.",
        "date": "2026-07-09",
        "pubDate": "2026-07-09T08:03:16+00:00",
